00:35:31,033 --> 00:35:32,053
Reddit is community-driven,

789
00:35:32,193 --> 00:35:33,234
so you don't have to post anything there.

790
00:35:33,394 --> 00:35:34,575
Somebody will find it and post it.

791
00:35:35,175 --> 00:35:36,936
And then, I think Twitch streamers also,

792
00:35:37,596 --> 00:35:38,457
if the game is patched,

793
00:35:38,757 --> 00:35:40,178
they'll briefly go over the patch notes,

794
00:35:40,318 --> 00:35:41,298
which were available in-game,

795
00:35:41,779 --> 00:35:43,239
so they would just read off of it and be like,

796
00:35:43,420 --> 00:35:44,820
oh, the game is completely different now.

797
00:35:45,241 --> 00:35:46,842
Now it's way harder or way easier.

798
00:35:47,942 --> 00:35:49,803
So, it's not way harder or easier.

799
00:35:50,083 --> 00:35:51,084
They're minor balance patches.

800
00:35:54,304 --> 00:35:57,366
So from these announcements, we try to funnel people into our Discord channel, because that's

801
00:35:57,386 --> 00:35:58,006
what we preferred.

802
00:35:58,707 --> 00:36:02,329
We found it to be the easiest format in where we can communicate with our players in real

803
00:36:02,369 --> 00:36:02,569
time.

