00:56:35,484 --> 00:56:36,924
did go up and down, not too much.

1278
00:56:37,305 --> 00:56:38,865
I think what's really important was that

1279
00:56:39,485 --> 00:56:42,086
we were able to maintain expectations the whole time.

1280
00:56:43,066 --> 00:56:44,707
We were always explicit about what was broken.

1281
00:56:45,527 --> 00:56:47,507
And we actually kept a lot of content hidden

1282
00:56:47,567 --> 00:56:49,528
from the main branch until it was 100% ready.

1283
00:56:50,228 --> 00:56:52,029
And that was kind of, I think,

1284
00:56:52,069 --> 00:56:55,510
our understanding between the players and ourselves.

1285
00:56:56,890 --> 00:56:58,370
So it's always about expectations.

1286
00:56:58,550 --> 00:56:59,651
Like, you have to communicate.

1287
00:56:59,871 --> 00:57:01,871
Like, reviews are always about communication.

1288
00:57:04,333 --> 00:57:06,514
And I guess if you don't fix something for a long time,

1289
00:57:07,455 --> 00:57:09,597
even if you communicate about it, it's not going to help.

1290
00:57:09,777 --> 00:57:11,958
So you do need to deliver on what you communicate.

1291
00:57:13,459 --> 00:57:14,440
Yes.

1292
00:57:14,520 --> 00:57:17,162
So you said you had about two years of dev time

1293
00:57:17,202 --> 00:57:18,343
with basically no income.

1294
00:57:18,423 --> 00:57:21,165
And you were also at that time contracting some stuff,

1295
00:57:21,225 --> 00:57:22,506
like sound design, art design.

1296
00:57:23,346 --> 00:57:25,948
So I guess my question is, what were those additional costs?

1297
00:57:26,028 --> 00:57:27,770
